**Iran Condemns Israel for Assassination of Hamas Leader, Threatens Retaliation**
Iran's acting Foreign Minister Ali Bagheri Kani accused Israel of crossing a red line after the assassination of Hamas leader Ismail Haniyeh in Iran. 'Israel has crossed the red line and put the peace and stability of the region and the world at risk,' Kani said in a phone call with Russian Foreign Minister Sergey Lavrov, according to the Iranian Foreign Ministry's Telegram channel. Iran intends to exercise its right to defend its territorial integrity and national security. The Iranian government has vowed to take action against Israel, and sources in the government have suggested that Iran may launch a combined attack with its allies, Yemen, Syria, and Iraq. The Russian government has condemned the assassination, saying it could destabilize the already tense situation in the region. A funeral procession for Haniyeh was held in Tehran, with thousands of people attending and carrying Palestinian and Iranian flags. The situation on the Middle East has been tense since October 7, 2023, when Hamas launched a rocket attack on Israel and invaded its territory, taking hostages. Israel responded with airstrikes.
